cards.rules_text: A deck can have any number of cards named Inkwell.

A deck can have any number of cards named Comedy Mask.
At the end of your turn, destroy Comedy Mask and create a Tragedy Mask token.

A deck can have any number of cards named Tragedy Mask.
At the end of your turn, destroy Tragedy Mask and create a Comedy Mask token.

A deck can have any number of cards named Comedy Mask.
At the end of your turn, destroy Comedy Mask and create a Tragedy Mask token.

A deck can have any number of cards named Tragedy Mask.
At the end of your turn, destroy Tragedy Mask and create a Comedy Mask token.

Transcend Ability: 2 Ink: Put a Transcendence counter on Venumar.
Transcend Ability: 4 Ink: Put two Transcendence counters on Venumar.
Attack Ability: 3 Ink: Venumar deals 1 damage to target attackable creation. Then if that creation has no Transcendence counters on it, Venumar deals 1 more damage to it.

Transcend Ability: 2 Ink: Put a Transcendence counter on Inkeye. Look at the top card of your deck. You may put it on the bottom of your deck.
Transcend Ability: 4 Ink: Put two Transcendence counters on Inkeye. Draw a card.

Transcend Ability: 1 Comedy: Put a Transcendence counter on Puppetear. Trigger the end of turn ability of a ComedyMask.
Transcend Ability: 5 Comedy: Put two Transcendence counters on Puppetear.
Attack Ability: 1 Tragedy: Puppetear deals 1 damage to target attackable creation. Trigger the end of turn ability of a TragedyMask.
Attack Ability: 5 Tragedy: Puppetear deals 2 damage to target attackable creation.

Ascendant [i](This creation can use a transcend ability the turn it's played.)[/i]
Transcend Ability: 2 Ink: Put a Transcendence counter on Protagonor.
Transcend Ability: 4 Ink: Put two Transcendence counters on Protagonor.
Attack Ability: 2 Ink: Protagonor deals 1 damage to target attackable creation.

Aggressive [i](This creation can use an attack ability the turn it's played.)[/i]
Transcend Ability: 2 Ink: Put a Transcendence counter on Antagonor.
Attack Ability: 2 Ink: Antagonor deals 1 damage to target attackable creation.
Attack Ability: 4 Ink: Antagonor deals 2 damage to target attackable creation.

As long as there are four or more mediums attached to Roosterror, if another creation you control would deal damage to a creation, it deals that much damage plus 1 instead.
Transcend Ability: 2 Ink: Put a Transcendence counter on Roosterror.
Attack Ability: 2 Ink: Roosterror deals 1 damage to target attackable creation.
Reserve the top three cards of your deck.

As a cost to play this card, discard three cards and destroy a creation you control.
Search your deck for any number of Inkwell cards, put them into your play zone, then shuffle. They can't be attached this turn.

As a cost to play this card, destroy two creation cards you control.
Draw three cards.

Put a Transcendence counter on target creation you control that didn't enter this turn. It can't fully transcend from counters put on it this turn. [i](They still count towards full transcendence later.)[/i]

Draw a card.
This turn, if a creation leaves a play zone, destroy all mediums that were attached to it.
Look at the top three cards of your deck. Reserve one of them and put the rest on the bottom of your deck in any order.

As a cost to play this card, discard a card.
Search your deck for up to two Medium cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand.
Destroy target Medium you don't control and target Medium you control.

Transcend Ability: 1 Ink: As a cost to activate this ability, destroy any number of mediums attached to Consumptoad. Put a Transcendence counter on Consumptoad for every second medium destroyed this way.
Attack Ability: 2 Ink: Consumptoad deals 1 damage to target attackable creation.

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Target non-Medium card being played is put into its owner's discard pile.

As a cost to play this card, destroy a medium card you control.
Draw three cards.
Put three cards from your reserve into your hand.

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Put a Transcendence counter on target creation you control that's being attacked. It can't fully transcend from counters put on it this turn. [i](They still count towards full transcendence later.)[/i]

Transcend abilities can't put more than one Transcendence counter on a creation.
Transcend Ability: 2 Ink: Put a Transcendence counter on Calculaw.
Attack Ability: 2 Ink: Calculaw deals 1 damage to target attackable creation.

As a cost to play this card, put two cards from your reserve into your discard pile.
Draw three cards.

Transcend Ability: 2 Ink: Put a Transcendence counter on Squirius. Reserve the top card of your deck.
Transcend Ability: 4 Ink: Put two Transcendence counters on Squirius. Reserve the top card of your deck.
Attack Ability: 3 Ink: Squirius deals 1 damage to target attackable creation. Put a card from your reserves into your hand.

Tempo [i](You can't play cards with tempo if you've played a card that shares a card name with them this turn.)[/i]
Play Inksight only if you control two or more Inkwells.
Draw two cards.

Transcend Ability: 4 Ink: Put a Transcendence counter on each other creation you control.
Attack Ability: 2 Ink: Banneroar deals 1 damage to target attackable creation.

Transcend Ability: 1 Ink: Put a Transcendence counter on another creation you control.
Transcend Ability: 3 Ink: Put a Transcendence counter on Blessink and another creation you control.
Attack Ability: 2 Ink: Blessink deals 1 damage to target attackable creation.

Transcend Ability: 2 Comedy: Put a Transcendence counter on Curtainyx.
Transcend Ability: 4 Comedy: Put two Transcendence counters on Curtainyx.
Attack Ability: 2 Tragedy: Curtainyx deals 1 damage to target attackable creation. Trigger the end of turn ability of a ComedyMask.

Ascendant [i](This creation can use a transcend ability the turn it's played.)[/i]
Plausiblade can't fully transcend.
Transcend Ability: 2 Ink: Put three Transcendence counters on Plausiblade.
Attack Ability: 4 Ink: Plausiblade deals X damage to target attackable creation, where X is the number of Transcendence counters on it.

Transcend Ability: 2 Comedy: Put a Transcendence counter on another creation you control.
Transcend Ability: 3 Comedy: Put a Transcendence counter on another creation you control.
Attack Ability: 2 Tragedy: Trigger the end of turn ability of a TragedyMask.

Draw a card.

Up to two target creations can't use attack or transcend abilities this turn.

Up to four target creations can't use attack abilities this turn.

Modifies medium
When Artmorphing enters a play zone, draw a card.
Modified medium is every medium subtype.

Modifies creation
Modified creation's attack abilities require 2 less Ink.

Modifies creation
Modified creation's transcend abilities require 2 less Ink.

Modifies creation
Modified creation's transcend and attack abilities require 1 less Ink.

Amnesia [i](You may play this card from your discard pile if it was put there from your deck this turn.)[/i]
Look at the top two cards of your deck. Put one of them into your hand and the rest into your discard pile.

Put the top four cards of your deck into your discard pile.

Transcend Ability: 4 Ink: Put two Transcendence counters on Forgetoad.
Attack Ability: 2 Ink: Forgetoad deals 1 damage to target attackable creation. Reserve a card from your discard pile.

Transcend Ability: 2 Ink: Put a Transcendence counter on another creation you control. Put the top two cards of your deck into your discard pile.
Attack Ability: 3 Ink: As a cost to activate this ability, void any number of cards from your discard pile. Mimesislug deals 1 damage to target attackable creation for every second card voided this way.

Amnesia [i](You may play this card from your discard pile if it was put there from your deck this turn.)[/i]
Transcend Ability: 2 Ink: Put a Transcendence counter on another creation you control. Shuffle a card from your discard pile into your deck.
Transcend Ability: 4 Ink: Put two Transcendence counters on another creation you control. Shuffle a card from your discard pile into your deck.
Transcend Ability: 4 Ink: Put two Transcendence counters on another creation you control. Shuffle two cards from your discard pile into your deck.

Malore requires 1 more Transcendence counters to fully transcend.
Whenever a tactic you control resolves, put a Transcendence counter on Malore.
At the start of your turn, remove all Transcendence counters from Malore.
Transcend Ability: 2 Ink: Draw a card.

If you would create one or more non-ComedyMask non-TragedyMask tokens, you may create twice that many of those tokens instead.
Transcend Ability: 1 Ink: Put a Transcendence counter on another creation you control.
Create a token that's a copy of target creation you control.

Whenever you destroy a creation you control, at end of turn, if their are three or more Inkwells attached to Necrink, create a token that's a copy of the destroyed creation.
Transcend Ability: 1 Ink: Put two Transcendence counters on another token creation you control.

Bloodwell provides 2 Ink instead of 1.
As a cost for Bloodwell to provide Ink, destroy a creation you control.

Play Inferno only if you control four or more Mediums.
As a cost to play Inferno, return two mediums you control to your hand.
Destroy all creatures.
Studio Fire deals 1 damage to target creation for each medium attached to it.

Choose one —
• Destroy target modifier.
• Remove a Transcendence counter from target creation.

Transcend Ability: 2 Comedy: Put a Transcendence counter on Exitask. Trigger the end of turn ability of a TragedyMask.
Transcend Ability: 4 Comedy: Put a Transcendence counter on Exitask and another creation you control. Discard two cards, then draw two cards.
Attack Ability: 2 Tragedy: Exitask deals 1 damage to target attackable creation.

Transcend Ability: 2 Comedy: Put a Transcendence counter on Maskraft. Trigger the end of turn ability of a Tragedy.
Transcend Ability: 4 Comedy: Put a Transcendence counter on Maskraft and another creation you control. Put target ComedyMask or TragedyMask from your discard pile into your play zone.

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Play Exeunt only if you control a ComedyMask and a TragedyMask.
Return target creation you control and target creation you don't control to their owners' hands.

Whenever one or more Transcendence counters are put on Leadette from an ability of another creation, put a Transcendence counter on Leadette for every third ComedyMask attached to it.
Attack Ability: 2 Tragedy: Leadette deals 1 damage to target attackable creation.

Act [i](You may play this card with Act. If you do, it gains Aggressive and Ascendant and is returned to your hand at end of turn.)[/i]
Transcend Ability: 4 Comedy: Put a Transcendence counter on each other creation you control.

When Comedeus enters your play zone, trigger the end of turn abilities of each TragedyMask you control.
Transcend Ability: 3 Comedy: Put a Transcendence counter on Comedeus, then create a Tragedeus token and move all Transcendence counters from Comedeus to the created token. Destroy Comedeus.

When Comedeus enters your play zone, trigger the end of turn abilities of each TragedyMask you control.
Transcend Ability: 3 Comedy: Put a Transcendence counter on Comedeus, then create a Tragedeus token and move all Transcendence counters from Comedeus to the created token. Destroy Comedeus.

When Tragedeus enters your play zone, trigger the end of turn abilities of each ComedyMask you control.
Attack Ability: 3 Tragedy: Tragedeus deals 1 damage to target attackable creation, then create a Comedeus token and move all Transcendence counters from Tragedeus to the created token. Destroy Tragedeus.

When Tragedeus enters your play zone, trigger the end of turn abilities of each ComedyMask you control.
Attack Ability: 3 Tragedy: Tragedeus deals 1 damage to target attackable creation, then create a Comedeus token and move all Transcendence counters from Tragedeus to the created token. Destroy Tragedeus.

Used Inkwell provides 2 Ink instead of 1.
As a cost for Used Inkwell to provide Ink, destroy Used Inkwell.
